#Breakdown by class
plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
sns.countplot(x="Topic", data=data);
plt.show()

#Breakdown by Nationality
plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
sns.countplot(x="Nationality", data=data);
plt.show()

#The biggest visual trend can be seen in how frequently the student was absent.
#Over 90% of the students who did poorly were absent more than seven times,
#while almost none of the students who did well were absent more than seven times.
sns.countplot(x='StudentAbsenceDays',data = data, hue='Class',palette='PuBu',
              hue_order=['Low-Level','Medium-Level','High-Level'])
plt.show()

#Parents satisfaction and Perfomance
sns.countplot(x='ParentSchoolSatisfaction',data = data, hue='Class',palette='bright')
plt.show()

#From the students who did well, a large majority of their parents were satisfied with the education they received. 
#The students whose parents were least satisfied with the school performed much worse

#Parents Satisfaction and Days of Absence
sns.countplot(x='ParentSchoolSatisfaction',data = data, hue='StudentAbsenceDays',palette='bright')
plt.show()

fig, axarr  = plt.subplots(2,2,figsize=(10,10))
sns.barplot(x='Class', y='VisitedResources', data=data, order=['Low-Level','Medium-Level','High-Level'], ax=axarr[0,0])
sns.barplot(x='Class', y='AnnouncementsViewed', data=data, order=['Low-Level','Medium-Level','High-Level'], ax=axarr[0,1])
sns.barplot(x='Class', y='RaisedHands', data=data, order=['Low-Level','Medium-Level','High-Level'], ax=axarr[1,0])
sns.barplot(x='Class', y='Discussion', data=data, order=['Low-Level','Medium-Level','High-Level'], ax=axarr[1,1])
#Students who performed better were way more active in all aspects.
